HEADWORD: Hydrophore
<hw>Hy"dro*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"y`dwr</grk> water + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety> <def>An
instrument used for the purpose of obtaining specimens of water from any
desired depth, as in a river, a lake, or the ocean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

